reviews.text: I haven't used it in nearly 20 years.. But I remember my dog used to run a cross the park and meet me from the train...she was so happy and lively.. And when I walked her in Garston park she'd yap excitedly whenever she heard the train.. She'd pull towards it even though I wasn't getting off the train because I was with her.. Poor doggy. I lost her at 9 years tragically.

A barebones halt located on the edge of a housing estate. Has only the basic of facilities as well as the really bad Abbey Line timetable to deal with. It has step free access to and from the platform at the very least and a single ticket machine which only accepts card payments.
A small railway station on the Abbey Line.
